Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First Phase 9 batch, following the Phase 7 R2 / Phase 8 recipe with one
structural deviation: hosts are owned by the per-WebContents WebUI
controller (std::unique_ptr<SlayzoneXxxHost> host_ member) rather than by
SlayzoneBrowserView. Overlays are full-window surfaces with no per-
BrowserView identity requirement — singleton sidecar calls suffice — and
this intentionally sidesteps editing SlayzoneBrowserView.{h,cc} while the
Phase 7 R3 terminal-slot work is in flight. Overlay-routing (ShowOverlay
+ overlay_webview_ member + previous-mode restore) is held for patch
0038 once P7 R3 signals 7.7 done.

Mojom (chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/{leaderboard,usage,context}.mojom):
- LeaderboardHost.GetSnapshot() => (LeaderboardSnapshot)
- UsageHost.GetSnapshot(range_key, provider_filter) => (UsageSnapshot)
- ContextHost.GetSnapshot(project_id) => (ContextSnapshot)
All mirror packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/*.mojom.

Hosts (SlayzoneXxxHost): SidecarClient-forwarded GetSnapshot; base::
ListValue throughout per patch 0022 hotfix. Empty-snapshot fallback on
missing/malformed response so the overlay renders its frame even when
the sidecar stubs aren't wired.

WebUI controllers (SlayzoneXxxUI): slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource with
per-overlay missing-bundle inline HTML. BindInterface routes to the UI-
owned host_ (std::unique_ptr).

Wire-up: browser/BUILD.gn + ui/BUILD.gn source entries; desktop binders
register ForWebUI<SlayzoneXxxUI>().Add<XxxHost>() triplet; webui registry
adds the 3 configs; ChromeURLHosts + url_constants.h constants.

Scope fences held — no SlayzoneBrowserView edits, no overlay_webview_
member, no Mode::kOverlay enum extension; all defer to 0038. Dialog-bound
actions (filter, add, edit) render disabled with a Phase 10 tooltip in JS.
